The paper discusses adversarial training, which is a popular technique in machine learning for improving the robustness of models against adversarial attacks. This technique is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.CL are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the tradeoff between standard and robust accuracy, which is a common concern in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper rules out optimization concerns, which suggests that cs.CR (cryptography and security) may also be a relevant sub-category.
